1
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:40,140
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,170 --> 00:01:43,210
[Episode 31]

3
00:01:43,430 --> 00:01:45,150
It was so chaotic back then.

4
00:01:45,870 --> 00:01:46,970
Bullets

5
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,400
were flying everywhere.

6
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:50,450
Who had time to observe details?

7
00:01:52,340 --> 00:01:53,430
I only remember

8
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:57,200
some people
being very accurate with their shots.

9
00:01:57,759 --> 00:01:59,280
Much better than us.

10
00:02:03,870 --> 00:02:05,270
Can you be more specific?

11
00:02:15,630 --> 00:02:16,630
Details that seem

12
00:02:16,630 --> 00:02:17,840
insignificant to you

13
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:19,430
might play a decisive role

14
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,680
in our work.

15
00:02:21,370 --> 00:02:22,620
We've also asked

16
00:02:22,740 --> 00:02:24,070
Shao Yunfei and Sangba.

17
00:02:24,210 --> 00:02:25,810
They went into great detail.

18
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:26,930
So we hope you two

19
00:02:27,210 --> 00:02:27,990
can try to

20
00:02:28,140 --> 00:02:29,300
remember a bit more.

21
00:02:38,540 --> 00:02:39,130
Eat up.

22
00:02:49,620 --> 00:02:50,950
Interviewing those two

23
00:02:51,050 --> 00:02:53,579
is more tiring
than interrogating suspects.

24
00:02:53,980 --> 00:02:54,500
Why didn't you

25
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:55,560
say a word just now?

26
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:03,140
The Mazhi Hongyuan Freight Company

27
00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:04,470
and the Qima'er Gold Minefrom back then,

28
00:03:04,470 --> 00:03:06,330
and the current Xinhai Coal Mine—

29
00:03:06,780 --> 00:03:07,620
we need to know

30
00:03:07,650 --> 00:03:09,360
more about them.

31
00:03:09,550 --> 00:03:10,390
After all,

32
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,800
17 years have passed.

33
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:13,850
The clues are scarce.

34
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,090
The Hongyuan employee list

35
00:03:16,090 --> 00:03:17,490
is missing another page.

36
00:03:17,530 --> 00:03:18,230
What are they whispering

37
00:03:18,230 --> 00:03:18,960
about?

38
00:03:19,790 --> 00:03:21,170
Us, I think.

39
00:03:22,780 --> 00:03:24,040
I can't hear anything.

40
00:03:24,810 --> 00:03:25,460
Yeah.

41
00:03:27,630 --> 00:03:28,740
Let's watch TV!

42
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:30,780
The police are catching a thief!

43
00:03:38,550 --> 00:03:39,750
The same gun appeared

44
00:03:40,780 --> 00:03:41,840
at the Qima'er Gold Mine

45
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,910
and at the scene

46
00:03:42,930 --> 00:03:44,579
of the unnamed corpse.

47
00:03:46,420 --> 00:03:47,780
And the boss of both the Qima'er Gold Mine

48
00:03:47,780 --> 00:03:48,900
and Hongyuan Freight Company

49
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:50,190
is Li Yongqiang.

50
00:03:51,010 --> 00:03:52,840
Xinhai's Vice President, Wu Jiang,

51
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:54,400
used to work

52
00:03:54,430 --> 00:03:55,430
for Li Yongqiang.

53
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:57,860
I hope that

54
00:03:58,500 --> 00:03:59,970
while we are investigating other employees

55
00:03:59,970 --> 00:04:01,630
at Hongyuan Freight Company,

56
00:04:01,710 --> 00:04:03,800
we can also look into people
connected to Wu Jiang

57
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,020
at Xinhai Group.

58
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:09,340
Investigating Hongyuan is reasonable.

59
00:04:10,370 --> 00:04:12,030
But investigating Xinhai...

60
00:04:12,970 --> 00:04:14,630
Don't you suspect Wu Jiang too?

61
00:04:14,630 --> 00:04:16,029
That's just a suspicion.

62
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:18,390
Xinhai is a key corporation in the city.

63
00:04:18,620 --> 00:04:19,860
With these doubts,

64
00:04:19,950 --> 00:04:21,329
they wouldn't approve

65
00:04:23,070 --> 00:04:24,800
our request for surveillance.

66
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:27,030
Let's try.

67
00:04:28,620 --> 00:04:29,220
Let's see

68
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:29,930
if there is

69
00:04:29,930 --> 00:04:30,770
any other way.

70
00:04:36,100 --> 00:04:37,310
Any other way...

71
00:04:48,690 --> 00:04:49,930
Is she looking at us?

72
00:04:51,860 --> 00:04:52,620
No, no.

73
00:04:54,540 --> 00:04:55,620
Xinhai

74
00:04:55,690 --> 00:04:56,360
is going to acquire

75
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:57,890
the coal mine on our pasture, right?

76
00:04:57,890 --> 00:04:58,570
Yeah.

77
00:04:59,690 --> 00:05:02,090
Bai Chun,
whom you couldn't beat last time,

78
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:04,030
is now a mine manager there.

79
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:05,570
What do you mean "couldn't beat"?

80
00:05:05,570 --> 00:05:07,000
It was a tie, okay?

81
00:05:07,070 --> 00:05:07,930
Keep bragging.

82
00:05:28,070 --> 00:05:28,690
Our mine

83
00:05:28,770 --> 00:05:30,480
is currently performing very well.

84
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:31,690
Sales are great too.

85
00:05:31,890 --> 00:05:33,060
There's just one problem.

86
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:33,930
It's simply that the mine's

87
00:05:33,930 --> 00:05:35,040
production capacity is insufficient.

88
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:36,040
So I'm thinking

89
00:05:36,130 --> 00:05:37,930
of expanding the capacity a bit.

90
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:38,920
Two.

91
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:39,810
Just two.

92
00:05:39,950 --> 00:05:40,890
Two million tons.

93
00:05:40,890 --> 00:05:41,940
Mayor Lin, what do you think?

94
00:05:41,940 --> 00:05:42,670
Is that okay?

95
00:05:42,870 --> 00:05:44,430
Two million tons?

96
00:05:44,470 --> 00:05:45,500
Not even one ton.

97
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:46,950
Don't you know?

98
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,330
The city

99
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,560
is already consolidating
and limiting production.

100
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,390
No mines are allowed

101
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:52,850
to expand capacity at all.

102
00:05:53,190 --> 00:05:53,790
Mayor Lin,

103
00:05:53,860 --> 00:05:54,860
I just want...

104
00:05:54,950 --> 00:05:56,480
That's enough. Go back now.

105
00:05:56,970 --> 00:05:57,720
This isn't a place

106
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:58,980
for me to discuss work.

107
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,190
Let me take a walk in peace.

108
00:06:02,560 --> 00:06:03,830
Alright.

109
00:06:10,540 --> 00:06:11,140
Uncle Lin.

110
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:12,960
Good morning.

111
00:06:13,430 --> 00:06:13,960
Morning.

112
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:15,180
Even during your morning exercise,

113
00:06:15,180 --> 00:06:15,830
people come to find you

114
00:06:15,830 --> 00:06:16,830
to report on work?

115
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,830
These small mine owners

116
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,660
stick like glue wherever I go.

117
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:24,000
While we're trying to consolidate,

118
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,120
they're still thinking about
expanding capacity.

119
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,320
How is that possible?

120
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:29,300
In the end,

121
00:06:30,860 --> 00:06:31,810
it's still about balancing

122
00:06:31,810 --> 00:06:34,190
environmental protection and development.

123
00:06:34,190 --> 00:06:34,920
If it weren't for you

124
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:36,250
insisting on focusing on development,

125
00:06:36,250 --> 00:06:36,760
the city's economy

126
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:37,630
wouldn't be doing so well.

127
00:06:37,630 --> 00:06:38,240
Not to mention,

128
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:38,950
this sports field

129
00:06:38,950 --> 00:06:40,680
wouldn't even have been built.

130
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:42,720
By the way,

131
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:44,420
I read the report

132
00:06:44,450 --> 00:06:45,430
you just published

133
00:06:45,430 --> 00:06:46,370
on the desert-combat heroes.

134
00:06:46,370 --> 00:06:47,900
It was really well written.

135
00:06:48,060 --> 00:06:49,330
You could dig more

136
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:50,430
into these

137
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:50,980
environmental stories

138
00:06:50,980 --> 00:06:51,770
in Tianduo.

139
00:06:53,570 --> 00:06:54,060
Yes.

140
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:56,690
Desert-combat heroes,

141
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:58,260
the Bird Lama,

142
00:06:58,420 --> 00:06:59,800
and the snow leopard expert.

143
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:00,720
This week, I'm going to

144
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:01,920
interview that...

145
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:04,050
that Doctor Yak.

146
00:07:06,180 --> 00:07:07,480
From the way you talk,

147
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:08,690
it sounds like

148
00:07:08,690 --> 00:07:10,740
you're not very willing
to write about these.

149
00:07:10,740 --> 00:07:11,690
Do you think these people

150
00:07:11,690 --> 00:07:12,690
and these stories

151
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,480
aren't worth publicizing?

152
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:15,280
Of course not.

153
00:07:16,620 --> 00:07:18,220
They are all very important.

154
00:07:18,510 --> 00:07:19,500
But these

155
00:07:20,430 --> 00:07:21,320
aren't the main reason

156
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,320
I came to Tianduo.

157
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:23,750
As you know,

158
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,430
I still want to write about Xinhai.

159
00:07:26,950 --> 00:07:27,990
So, how is it going?

160
00:07:27,990 --> 00:07:30,250
Is the interview progressing smoothly?

161
00:07:30,630 --> 00:07:32,230
There's a lot of resistance.

162
00:07:33,390 --> 00:07:34,570
I've called the Coal Bureau and Xinhai

163
00:07:34,570 --> 00:07:35,750
several times,

164
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:37,830
but got no reply.

165
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:39,650
I couldn't get

166
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,210
any meaningful data at all.

167
00:07:41,930 --> 00:07:42,790
That's normal.

168
00:07:44,370 --> 00:07:45,230
Think about it—

169
00:07:45,570 --> 00:07:46,850
the consolidation work

170
00:07:46,850 --> 00:07:47,850
has just started.

171
00:07:48,540 --> 00:07:50,270
The Coal Bureau and the companies

172
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:51,409
are swamped.

173
00:07:51,730 --> 00:07:53,110
It's normal that they don't have time

174
00:07:53,110 --> 00:07:54,180
to see you.

175
00:07:55,270 --> 00:07:56,360
Even if Xinhai

176
00:07:56,890 --> 00:07:58,090
really has problems,

177
00:07:58,430 --> 00:07:58,920
it's not up to you

178
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:00,010
to fix it alone.

179
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:02,220
You need to trust the regulatory power

180
00:08:02,220 --> 00:08:03,420
of the industry and commerce departments

181
00:08:03,420 --> 00:08:05,690
and environmental protection departments.

182
00:08:05,690 --> 00:08:06,290
Uncle Lin.

183
00:08:06,790 --> 00:08:08,250
Since you call me "Uncle,"

184
00:08:09,540 --> 00:08:10,740
there are some things

185
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,300
I have to tell you.

186
00:08:13,110 --> 00:08:14,510
Go ahead. I'm listening.

187
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:16,570
As a reporter,

188
00:08:17,790 --> 00:08:19,790
don't always look for the dark side.

189
00:08:20,730 --> 00:08:22,990
Coal mine consolidation is a good thing.

190
00:08:23,170 --> 00:08:24,300
Even if there are problems,

191
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:25,240
they're minor.

192
00:08:27,810 --> 00:08:29,070
You finally came back.

193
00:08:29,980 --> 00:08:30,930
The top priority

194
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:33,140
is to take care of your family.

195
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:35,799
Uncle Lin.

196
00:08:37,370 --> 00:08:38,500
I want to say that...

197
00:08:39,010 --> 00:08:40,270
You know my relationship

198
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:41,400
with the Bai family.

199
00:08:41,909 --> 00:08:42,770
Bai Ju hasn't had it easy

200
00:08:42,770 --> 00:08:44,059
over the years.

201
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:45,500
You know

202
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:46,320
her hang-ups.

203
00:08:47,030 --> 00:08:48,420
You should try to persuade her more

204
00:08:48,420 --> 00:08:49,750
from your perspective.

205
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,290
Things aren't like they were

206
00:08:51,290 --> 00:08:52,450
a few years ago.

207
00:08:52,940 --> 00:08:54,470
Your child has grown up now.

208
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:55,570
Even if you

209
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,330
don't think about yourselves,

210
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,400
you have to think about your kid.

211
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:00,620
If she wants

212
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:02,550
to work in the provincial capital,

213
00:09:02,650 --> 00:09:03,870
I can recommend her.

214
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,620
Then she'll have time

215
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:08,110
to be with the child.

216
00:09:09,050 --> 00:09:10,380
Wouldn't that be great?

217
00:09:10,830 --> 00:09:11,830
What do you think?

218
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:15,650
Shao,

219
00:09:16,030 --> 00:09:16,760
are you okay?

220
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:18,750
Relax. Relax.

221
00:09:19,390 --> 00:09:19,790
You...

222
00:09:19,790 --> 00:09:20,900
Altitude sickness.

223
00:09:20,900 --> 00:09:21,570
It's altitude sickness.

224
00:09:21,570 --> 00:09:22,310
Look at you.

225
00:09:22,430 --> 00:09:23,600
This young body

226
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:24,530
is useless.

227
00:09:25,010 --> 00:09:26,000
Relax. Relax.

228
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:26,480
Come on.

229
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,360
Breathe slowly. Breathe slowly.

230
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,580
You're really something.

231
00:09:35,270 --> 00:09:36,270
You actually let Uncle Lin

232
00:09:36,270 --> 00:09:37,600
talk you into fainting.

233
00:09:38,340 --> 00:09:39,170
I haven't been back

234
00:09:39,170 --> 00:09:40,240
for a long time.

235
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,270
At this altitude,

236
00:09:41,270 --> 00:09:42,030
of course I'm not used to

237
00:09:42,030 --> 00:09:43,430
doing aerobic exercise.

238
00:09:44,770 --> 00:09:45,440
Mr. Cheng.

239
00:09:45,730 --> 00:09:46,860
You're off work now?

240
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,820
The usual.

241
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:50,390
Okay, take a seat. It'll be ready soon.

242
00:09:50,390 --> 00:09:51,240
Noodles with spicy minced meat
and chili oil!

243
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,500
Extra oil, extra meat!

244
00:09:58,980 --> 00:10:00,840
Here you are.

245
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:03,490
Here's a Coke. On the house.

246
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:04,210
Thanks.

247
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:05,570
You're welcome.

248
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:11,770
This. See?

249
00:10:16,890 --> 00:10:18,120
I see you

250
00:10:18,340 --> 00:10:19,340
never get a break.

251
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,100
Doesn't Xinhai Transport

252
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:22,620
pay you a little extra?

253
00:10:24,230 --> 00:10:25,330
Extra?

254
00:10:26,030 --> 00:10:27,070
I'd be lucky if they didn't dock my pay.

255
00:10:27,070 --> 00:10:27,840
They do that?

256
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:32,770
I was thinking of having my brother

257
00:10:32,770 --> 00:10:34,780
quit his job at the saltworks back home

258
00:10:34,780 --> 00:10:36,740
and come to Xinhai to find some work.

259
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:38,000
But the pay isn't good.

260
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:40,050
Your brother?

261
00:10:41,740 --> 00:10:43,000
Isn't he your brother?

262
00:10:43,740 --> 00:10:44,150
No.

263
00:10:44,180 --> 00:10:45,910
He... he's my brother-in-law.

264
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:48,530
Ex... ex-brother-in-law.

265
00:10:48,550 --> 00:10:51,100
Ex-brother-in-law.
His sister and I got divorced.

266
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:51,870
But it looks like you two

267
00:10:51,870 --> 00:10:53,130
get along pretty well.

268
00:10:53,410 --> 00:10:54,170
Why don't you

269
00:10:54,690 --> 00:10:55,670
ask Mr. Bai to help your brother

270
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:56,670
get a job?

271
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:59,340
Mr. Bai is stingy.

272
00:11:00,210 --> 00:11:01,740
What are you talking about?

273
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,440
That store of mine in the city

274
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:05,030
isn't running as well as

275
00:11:05,030 --> 00:11:05,960
this small shop.

276
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:06,860
I'm counting on you guys

277
00:11:06,860 --> 00:11:07,790
to look after me.

278
00:11:13,170 --> 00:11:14,630
With the rectification now,

279
00:11:14,630 --> 00:11:16,090
work must be tough, right?

280
00:11:16,540 --> 00:11:18,170
There's plenty of work at the mines.

281
00:11:18,170 --> 00:11:19,680
Mostly three shifts.

282
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:22,180
The harder I work, the more I earn.

283
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:24,480
All the mines
are undergoing rectification now.

284
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:26,340
How come it's still three shifts?

285
00:11:36,270 --> 00:11:37,030
Mr. Cheng,

286
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:39,280
you're from Baolin too, right?

287
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,100
You and my brother-in-law

288
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:42,450
are from the same place.

289
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:43,610
You're from Baolin?

290
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:48,440
That's rare in Tianduo.

291
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:49,120
You're from there?

292
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:49,820
Yeah.

293
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:50,900
You don't have an accent.

294
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:51,360
Well...

295
00:11:51,870 --> 00:11:52,650
Let me tell you,

296
00:11:52,650 --> 00:11:53,620
here's the thing.

297
00:11:53,620 --> 00:11:54,340
My brother and I—

298
00:11:54,340 --> 00:11:55,410
my real brother—

299
00:11:55,510 --> 00:11:56,390
came here with our parents

300
00:11:56,390 --> 00:11:57,190
when we were little.

301
00:11:57,190 --> 00:11:58,650
So I don't have a hometown accent.

302
00:11:58,650 --> 00:12:00,220
But my taste hasn't changed.

303
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:00,860
I still like

304
00:12:00,860 --> 00:12:01,890
food from back home.

305
00:12:01,890 --> 00:12:02,670
Just now when I saw you

306
00:12:02,670 --> 00:12:03,340
eating that chili oil,

307
00:12:03,340 --> 00:12:03,940
I felt like

308
00:12:04,050 --> 00:12:05,370
we must be from the same place.

309
00:12:05,370 --> 00:12:05,770
Right.

310
00:12:05,770 --> 00:12:06,290
Right?

311
00:12:06,890 --> 00:12:07,740
Back home,

312
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,070
they make it with dry chili.

313
00:12:09,070 --> 00:12:09,550
Yes.

314
00:12:09,740 --> 00:12:10,650
It tastes better than this.

315
00:12:10,650 --> 00:12:11,630
Much better.

316
00:12:11,740 --> 00:12:12,480
Later on,

317
00:12:12,740 --> 00:12:14,150
I'll bring some over for you.

318
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:15,000
Okay.

319
00:12:17,700 --> 00:12:18,560
How about this?

320
00:12:18,940 --> 00:12:20,000
If it really doesn't work,

321
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,710
just have your brother come over.

322
00:12:21,710 --> 00:12:23,240
I'll take him under my wing.

323
00:12:23,550 --> 00:12:24,160
That's wonderful.

324
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,490
I'll let him know later.

325
00:12:26,460 --> 00:12:27,260
That's great.

326
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:32,530
You just said

327
00:12:32,550 --> 00:12:35,080
there's a lot of work here. Is it for

328
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:36,560
Xinhai's rectification?

329
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:38,720
Exactly.

330
00:12:39,230 --> 00:12:41,630
Every day we're hauling stuff to Chenlong.

331
00:12:41,660 --> 00:12:42,830
That's a good gig.

332
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:44,680
It's close.

333
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:46,480
You don't need to leave the mine.

334
00:12:46,580 --> 00:12:48,180
Everyone's fighting for it.

335
00:12:50,890 --> 00:12:52,050
Chenlong.

336
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:53,870
Cheng,

337
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,410
time to get back to work.

338
00:12:57,650 --> 00:12:58,410
Coming.

339
00:12:59,410 --> 00:13:00,470
It's 11.50, right?

340
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:02,330
Just give me 10.

341
00:13:03,340 --> 00:13:04,200
Just give me 10.

342
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:04,750
Let me...

343
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:05,950
Let me take this Coke.

344
00:13:05,980 --> 00:13:06,600
Okay.

345
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:07,960
Be caeful.

346
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:09,320
Yunfei,

347
00:13:09,410 --> 00:13:10,100
you've got to

348
00:13:10,100 --> 00:13:10,820
top up here.

349
00:13:11,270 --> 00:13:12,000
Top up?

350
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:13,750
For what?

351
00:13:14,130 --> 00:13:15,720
Support my business.

352
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,150
Your business is fine.

353
00:13:17,150 --> 00:13:18,480
Why should I support it?

354
00:13:18,870 --> 00:13:20,280
So, I helped for nothing?

355
00:13:21,220 --> 00:13:21,950
If you help,

356
00:13:22,020 --> 00:13:23,550
you should help all the way.

357
00:13:23,650 --> 00:13:24,500
After all these meals,

358
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:25,200
Mr. Cheng and I

359
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,010
are only nodding acquaintances.

360
00:13:26,010 --> 00:13:26,600
Nodding acquaintances?

361
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,460
How is that not helping all the way?

362
00:13:27,460 --> 00:13:28,550
We just started talking.

363
00:13:28,550 --> 00:13:29,440
But your brother...

364
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,140
Just started.

365
00:13:30,140 --> 00:13:30,840
He said...

366
00:13:30,870 --> 00:13:31,570
Just a few words.

367
00:13:31,570 --> 00:13:32,430
Let me tell you.

368
00:13:40,890 --> 00:13:41,430
Okay.

369
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:43,070
Coming right up.

370
00:13:43,070 --> 00:13:43,510
Alright.

371
00:13:43,510 --> 00:13:44,050
Where are you going?

372
00:13:44,050 --> 00:13:44,570
Where are you going?

373
00:13:44,570 --> 00:13:45,630
I have things to do.

374
00:13:45,770 --> 00:13:47,370
Are you going to top up or not?

375
00:13:47,890 --> 00:13:49,220
I'll top up 20 next time.

376
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:49,790
20?

377
00:13:49,820 --> 00:13:51,280
Don't come back next time.

378
00:13:53,580 --> 00:13:54,510
Are you cold?

379
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:55,250
I'm not.

380
00:13:55,390 --> 00:13:56,990
The weather changes so fast.

381
00:13:58,470 --> 00:13:59,120
Your mom didn't

382
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:00,030
even dress you warmly enough.

383
00:14:00,030 --> 00:14:01,030
I'm not cold.

384
00:14:01,050 --> 00:14:02,110
Alright, alright.

385
00:14:07,690 --> 00:14:08,280
Dad.

386
00:14:08,410 --> 00:14:09,000
What?

387
00:14:09,360 --> 00:14:10,690
Why are you so happy?

388
00:14:11,390 --> 00:14:12,550
Is it obvious?

389
00:14:12,620 --> 00:14:13,550
I may be young,

390
00:14:13,570 --> 00:14:14,760
but I'm not stupid.

391
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:15,750
Your teacher

392
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:16,480
called me to school today.

393
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,410
I'm quite happy.

394
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:19,290
It's not a good thing.

395
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:21,480
But this is my first time

396
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:22,750
being called to school

397
00:14:22,750 --> 00:14:24,010
as a parent.

398
00:14:25,330 --> 00:14:26,000
Besides,

399
00:14:26,130 --> 00:14:27,510
I'm an expert at getting criticized.

400
00:14:27,510 --> 00:14:29,060
I get scolded a lot at work.

401
00:14:30,980 --> 00:14:32,780
Then why aren't you scolding me?

402
00:14:33,290 --> 00:14:34,390
Why would I?

403
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,030
Because I got into a fight.

404
00:14:37,650 --> 00:14:38,820
That's because that boy

405
00:14:38,820 --> 00:14:39,500
started it.

406
00:14:39,530 --> 00:14:40,890
He pulled your ponytail first.

407
00:14:40,890 --> 00:14:41,410
Right.

408
00:14:41,670 --> 00:14:42,460
And that wasn't

409
00:14:42,460 --> 00:14:43,320
the first time.

410
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:44,480
I hit him last time too.

411
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:45,620
But he never learns.

412
00:14:45,650 --> 00:14:46,180
Alright.

413
00:14:46,970 --> 00:14:48,230
Listen to me, Zhuling.

414
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:50,430
When someone bullies us,

415
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,030
we must protect ourselves.

416
00:14:52,030 --> 00:14:53,270
This is called self-defense.

417
00:14:53,270 --> 00:14:54,290
But self-defense

418
00:14:54,390 --> 00:14:55,010
has limits...

419
00:14:55,010 --> 00:14:55,910
If he messes with me again,

420
00:14:55,910 --> 00:14:56,970
I'll hit him again.

421
00:14:57,180 --> 00:14:58,780
I haven't used this move yet.

422
00:15:02,160 --> 00:15:03,290
Who taught you that?

423
00:15:03,390 --> 00:15:04,240
Your mom?

424
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:04,790
Yeah.

425
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:08,620
That sounds like your mom.

426
00:15:11,020 --> 00:15:11,900
Let me tell you, these...

427
00:15:11,900 --> 00:15:13,040
these moves

428
00:15:13,070 --> 00:15:14,230
are only for bad guys.

429
00:15:14,230 --> 00:15:15,540
You can't use them on your classmates.

430
00:15:15,540 --> 00:15:16,140
Got it?

431
00:15:17,370 --> 00:15:18,150
I'm talking to you.

432
00:15:18,150 --> 00:15:18,980
Listen to me.

433
00:15:20,670 --> 00:15:22,070
Self-defense is right.

434
00:15:22,940 --> 00:15:23,530
But

435
00:15:23,630 --> 00:15:24,480
it must be within

436
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:25,700
reasonable limits.

437
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:26,270
Otherwise,

438
00:15:26,270 --> 00:15:27,530
you would hurt others.

439
00:15:27,750 --> 00:15:28,080
Next time,

440
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,170
when he pulls your ponytail again,

441
00:15:29,170 --> 00:15:30,390
you can tell the teacher

442
00:15:30,390 --> 00:15:31,250
or us.

443
00:15:31,270 --> 00:15:32,290
But at that moment,

444
00:15:32,290 --> 00:15:33,270
do you know

445
00:15:33,290 --> 00:15:35,340
what the most important thing to do is?

446
00:15:35,340 --> 00:15:36,000
What is it?

447
00:15:37,660 --> 00:15:38,570
What is it?

448
00:15:40,150 --> 00:15:41,390
Run!

449
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:45,010
Pull your ponytail!

450
00:15:49,010 --> 00:15:49,350
Here.

451
00:15:49,940 --> 00:15:51,030
The soup is ready. Have some.

452
00:15:51,030 --> 00:15:52,490
I'm full. I don't want any.

453
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:54,770
I'm going to your study to do my homework.

454
00:15:54,770 --> 00:15:55,300
Go ahead.

455
00:16:02,290 --> 00:16:04,020
What did the teacher say today?

456
00:16:06,090 --> 00:16:07,550
Both of them got punished.

457
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:08,960
Both sides were at fault.

458
00:16:09,130 --> 00:16:09,980
I have, um...

459
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:11,370
severely

460
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:13,160
criticized her.

461
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:14,100
You?

462
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:15,820
Criticize her?

463
00:16:20,630 --> 00:16:22,470
I'll teach her a good lesson later.

464
00:16:22,470 --> 00:16:23,070
Don't.

465
00:16:23,730 --> 00:16:24,640
She promised me

466
00:16:25,070 --> 00:16:26,930
she would never hit anyone again.

467
00:16:29,130 --> 00:16:30,330
Don't you believe it?

468
00:16:30,820 --> 00:16:32,750
I'm good at reasoning with people.

469
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:42,750
Recently,

470
00:16:43,450 --> 00:16:45,650
have you been in touch with Meng Yaohui?

471
00:16:49,590 --> 00:16:50,860
I'm very tired today.

472
00:16:50,980 --> 00:16:52,760
I don't have time to bicker with you.

473
00:16:52,760 --> 00:16:54,420
I just want to have a good meal.

474
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:03,170
Shao Yunfei.

475
00:17:03,270 --> 00:17:04,140
Look at this.

476
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,270
I'm sitting right across from you.

477
00:17:05,270 --> 00:17:06,180
Just say it directly, okay?

478
00:17:06,180 --> 00:17:07,310
Just take a look.

479
00:17:11,140 --> 00:17:11,660
These are all things I wrote

480
00:17:11,660 --> 00:17:14,190
after I arrived
at the Tianduo press station.

481
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:15,609
There's even one about Doctor Yak.

482
00:17:15,609 --> 00:17:17,410
It'll be published in a few days.

483
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:20,400
I didn't come here

484
00:17:21,810 --> 00:17:23,460
just to write these things.

485
00:17:27,730 --> 00:17:29,060
Then you can go back.

486
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:29,900
No one is forcing you

487
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:30,790
to stay here.

488
00:17:30,940 --> 00:17:31,960
Don't you know

489
00:17:31,980 --> 00:17:32,560
why exactly

490
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:33,620
I am staying here?

491
00:17:37,070 --> 00:17:37,740
I...

492
00:17:39,410 --> 00:17:40,310
I want you...

493
00:17:40,340 --> 00:17:41,640
We agreed on this.

494
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:42,990
Right now, I can't...

495
00:17:42,990 --> 00:17:43,670
I want you to

496
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:45,030
help me get into Xinhai.

497
00:17:49,770 --> 00:17:50,590
Well, for that,

498
00:17:50,590 --> 00:17:52,080
you can go straight to Bai Chun.

499
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:53,310
Why go through all this trouble?

500
00:17:53,310 --> 00:17:54,730
He's never liked me.

501
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:55,900
You know that.

502
00:17:58,950 --> 00:17:59,890
Why are you so obsessed

503
00:17:59,890 --> 00:18:00,740
with Xinhai?

504
00:18:02,570 --> 00:18:03,350
Rectification.

505
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:04,110
I found that now,

506
00:18:04,110 --> 00:18:05,420
they're just using a new name

507
00:18:05,420 --> 00:18:06,020
to make all the small coal mines

508
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:06,970
part of Xinhai.

509
00:18:07,220 --> 00:18:07,870
The problems that need fixing

510
00:18:07,870 --> 00:18:09,400
probably weren't touched.

511
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:10,630
Then you can report these things

512
00:18:10,630 --> 00:18:12,390
to the Coal Bureau

513
00:18:12,530 --> 00:18:14,030
or tell Uncle Lin.

514
00:18:14,980 --> 00:18:15,880
What can I report?

515
00:18:15,880 --> 00:18:17,610
I can't just make empty claims.

516
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:19,180
Not only do you need evidence

517
00:18:19,180 --> 00:18:20,640
for your investigations,

518
00:18:20,830 --> 00:18:22,760
but we also need it for our reports.

519
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:24,240
I heard that several small mines,

520
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:25,370
after being merged,

521
00:18:25,380 --> 00:18:26,380
stopped briefly

522
00:18:26,510 --> 00:18:28,180
and then started operating again.

523
00:18:28,180 --> 00:18:29,960
The transport drivers are all busy.

524
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:30,760
As a reporter,

525
00:18:30,770 --> 00:18:31,240
if I see it,

526
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:32,640
I can't pretend I didn't.

527
00:18:45,180 --> 00:18:46,720
This is an open-pit mine.

528
00:18:47,630 --> 00:18:48,760
Really impressive.

529
00:18:49,150 --> 00:18:50,210
Eye-opening, huh?

530
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:52,080
Yes, indeed.

531
00:18:58,330 --> 00:18:58,960
Chun,

532
00:18:59,100 --> 00:19:00,790
why don't you go back to your work?

533
00:19:00,790 --> 00:19:01,280
I guess

534
00:19:01,310 --> 00:19:03,310
we'll still be shooting for a while.

535
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:05,310
If I don't let him take enough photos,

536
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:06,840
he'll come bother me again,

537
00:19:06,890 --> 00:19:08,950
and then I'll have to come bother you.

538
00:19:09,850 --> 00:19:10,950
It's okay. I don't mind.

539
00:19:10,950 --> 00:19:12,010
I'll stay with you.

540
00:19:13,010 --> 00:19:14,420
Manager Bai! Manager Bai!

541
00:19:14,420 --> 00:19:15,220
What's wrong?

542
00:19:15,670 --> 00:19:17,110
The hydraulic shovel down here
is malfunctioning.

543
00:19:17,110 --> 00:19:18,880
The hydraulic shovel is malfunctioning.

544
00:19:18,880 --> 00:19:20,010
Is it turned off now?

545
00:19:20,450 --> 00:19:21,910
Is there any safety issue?

546
00:19:22,220 --> 00:19:23,320
It's already turned off.

547
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:25,250
Please hurry down and take a look.

548
00:19:25,850 --> 00:19:26,330
Chun,

549
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:27,820
go do your work.

550
00:19:28,220 --> 00:19:29,720
Yes, go do your work.

551
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:31,020
There's only this one road, right?

552
00:19:31,020 --> 00:19:32,420
We can walk by ourselves.

553
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:38,210
You can only take photos here.

554
00:19:38,350 --> 00:19:39,250
We're not trying to

555
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:40,070
cover anything up.

556
00:19:40,070 --> 00:19:41,940
It's just that our industry
is quite sensitive.

557
00:19:41,940 --> 00:19:42,240
About that...

558
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:42,970
Don't worry.

559
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:44,050
I still have

560
00:19:44,070 --> 00:19:45,180
my professional ethics.

561
00:19:45,180 --> 00:19:46,140
If he dares to take photos recklessly,

562
00:19:46,140 --> 00:19:47,210
I'll break his hands.

563
00:19:47,210 --> 00:19:47,940
Don't worry.

564
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:51,570
Finish shooting quickly and leave.

565
00:19:51,570 --> 00:19:51,940
Okay.

566
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:52,890
I'm coming down.

567
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:55,220
Be careful.

568
00:20:39,090 --> 00:20:40,050
Han?

569
00:20:40,460 --> 00:20:41,960
Why is Han standing there?

570
00:20:43,930 --> 00:20:44,980
Didn't you see him?

571
00:20:44,980 --> 00:20:45,550
Han opened

572
00:20:45,550 --> 00:20:46,260
the roadblock for us.

573
00:20:46,260 --> 00:20:47,190
Did you see that?

574
00:20:54,790 --> 00:20:55,540
Are you

575
00:20:55,570 --> 00:20:57,100
keeping something from me?

576
00:21:23,940 --> 00:21:26,340
[Chenlong Coal Mine]

577
00:21:57,930 --> 00:21:58,900
Mr. Meng.

578
00:22:00,100 --> 00:22:00,860
Why didn't you tell me

579
00:22:00,860 --> 00:22:01,810
you were coming?

580
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:03,380
I would have picked you up.

581
00:22:03,890 --> 00:22:05,520
I already told my brother.

582
00:22:06,090 --> 00:22:08,010
I just want to come in and have a look.

583
00:22:08,010 --> 00:22:09,270
What do you want to see?

584
00:22:10,050 --> 00:22:10,900
Here at our mine,

585
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:12,760
there are no security incidents.

586
00:22:14,180 --> 00:22:15,330
Hello, Mr. Meng.

587
00:22:15,930 --> 00:22:17,460
I asked her to bring me here.

588
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:18,590
Doesn't the city

589
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:19,110
want a report

590
00:22:19,110 --> 00:22:20,160
on Xinhai's consolidation?

591
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:21,290
I'm a bit short on material

592
00:22:21,290 --> 00:22:22,890
and want to take some photos.

593
00:22:25,160 --> 00:22:25,740
Sure.

594
00:22:26,050 --> 00:22:26,710
No problem.

595
00:22:27,830 --> 00:22:28,900
Actually,

596
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,510
regarding dust suppression,

597
00:22:30,510 --> 00:22:31,330
open-pit mines

598
00:22:31,330 --> 00:22:33,290
aren't as complicated
as underground mines.

599
00:22:33,290 --> 00:22:35,160
Mainly it's water spraying

600
00:22:35,250 --> 00:22:36,850
and covering with dust nets.

601
00:22:37,050 --> 00:22:37,900
As for us,

602
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,440
we apply a combination of water spraying

603
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:41,540
and chemical suppressants.

604
00:22:43,130 --> 00:22:45,220
We also optimized blasting techniques.

605
00:22:45,220 --> 00:22:46,720
But we can't

606
00:22:46,750 --> 00:22:48,610
demonstrate that to you on-site.

607
00:22:49,610 --> 00:22:50,170
Mr. Meng.

608
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,240
Well...

609
00:22:53,550 --> 00:22:54,870
Mine No. 2 we're looking at now

610
00:22:54,870 --> 00:22:56,190
isn't much different

611
00:22:56,220 --> 00:22:57,820
from Mine No. 1 we saw before.

612
00:23:00,660 --> 00:23:02,210
Why can't you show us

613
00:23:02,530 --> 00:23:03,530
Chenlong Mine?

614
00:23:05,560 --> 00:23:08,110
Chenlong is undergoing
dust equipment maintenance

615
00:23:08,110 --> 00:23:09,370
and slope management.

616
00:23:10,550 --> 00:23:12,550
Didn't you want to see the rectification?

617
00:23:12,550 --> 00:23:13,950
Mine No. 2 is the focus

618
00:23:13,970 --> 00:23:16,030
of our rectification work right now.

619
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,130
It seems that you have

620
00:23:21,130 --> 00:23:22,320
plenty of material.

621
00:23:23,050 --> 00:23:25,840
You brought that camera in
but didn't take many photos.

622
00:23:25,840 --> 00:23:27,010
I... I did.

623
00:23:27,770 --> 00:23:29,280
I just took a lot.

624
00:23:29,310 --> 00:23:29,730
Look.

625
00:23:31,180 --> 00:23:31,900
Look.

626
00:23:32,100 --> 00:23:32,960
Here they are.

627
00:23:33,150 --> 00:23:33,830
See?

628
00:23:35,890 --> 00:23:36,890
It's out of focus.

629
00:23:38,940 --> 00:23:39,710
What's wrong with you?

630
00:23:39,710 --> 00:23:40,400
How is it...

631
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:42,290
How is it out of focus?

632
00:23:42,290 --> 00:23:42,920
How did you...

633
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:43,660
Didn't I take photos

634
00:23:43,660 --> 00:23:45,390
of that Bird Lama a few days ago?

635
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:46,330
I held the camera up for ages,

636
00:23:46,330 --> 00:23:47,380
but the bird didn't come.

637
00:23:47,380 --> 00:23:49,380
My arm started hurting afterwards.

638
00:23:49,450 --> 00:23:50,510
Let me retake a few.

639
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:52,910
Let me try.

640
00:23:54,350 --> 00:23:54,800
Okay.

641
00:23:54,820 --> 00:23:55,840
You... you do it.

642
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:10,820
Take a look.

643
00:24:11,210 --> 00:24:12,140
Not bad. Not bad.

644
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:15,300
The scenery up there is nice.

645
00:24:35,380 --> 00:24:41,340
[Meng Yaohui, General Manager]

646
00:24:41,590 --> 00:24:42,890
It's great to be young.

647
00:24:43,480 --> 00:24:44,050
Right?

648
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:46,800
It reminds me of my younger days,

649
00:24:46,940 --> 00:24:48,740
studying at the sports academy.

650
00:24:49,770 --> 00:24:50,920
Mr. Meng, you went from a sports student

651
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:52,520
to the coal mining industry.

652
00:24:53,020 --> 00:24:54,170
That's quite a leap.

653
00:24:56,290 --> 00:24:57,400
I only remember

654
00:24:58,400 --> 00:25:00,490
some people
being very accurate with their shots.

655
00:25:00,490 --> 00:25:02,010
Much better than us.

656
00:25:06,690 --> 00:25:08,680
Who authorized you to bring that reporter

657
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:10,270
into the mine to take photos?

658
00:25:10,270 --> 00:25:10,940
Mr. Feng,

659
00:25:11,550 --> 00:25:13,030
guiding public opinion

660
00:25:13,650 --> 00:25:15,650
is about channeling, not blocking.

661
00:25:16,140 --> 00:25:17,240
This is

662
00:25:17,330 --> 00:25:18,590
all beneficial for us.

663
00:25:20,410 --> 00:25:21,740
That reporter, Shao,

664
00:25:21,830 --> 00:25:23,690
has been keeping a close eye on us.

665
00:25:24,050 --> 00:25:24,790
And last time,
the Environmental Protection Bureau

666
00:25:24,790 --> 00:25:25,720
couldn't get in.

667
00:25:26,270 --> 00:25:27,180
If this keeps up,

668
00:25:27,180 --> 00:25:28,590
with a surprise inspection one day

669
00:25:28,590 --> 00:25:29,510
and a complaint the next,

670
00:25:29,510 --> 00:25:30,060
it'll unsettle everyone

671
00:25:30,060 --> 00:25:31,140
at the mine.

672
00:25:32,590 --> 00:25:33,550
I thought

673
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,200
it would be better
if we took the initiative,

674
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:36,290
so they wouldn't try

675
00:25:36,290 --> 00:25:37,330
any sneaky ways to get in,

676
00:25:37,330 --> 00:25:39,190
which would be more troublesome.

677
00:25:40,330 --> 00:25:41,420
They only saw

678
00:25:42,010 --> 00:25:43,410
what I wanted them to see.

679
00:25:43,890 --> 00:25:45,110
Everything was legal and compliant.

680
00:25:45,110 --> 00:25:46,640
No one could find any fault.

681
00:25:58,950 --> 00:26:01,070
Has that police officer
from the task force

682
00:26:01,070 --> 00:26:02,470
made any moves recently?

683
00:26:03,070 --> 00:26:04,820
She tracked down Hongyuan Freight Company.

684
00:26:04,820 --> 00:26:06,220
There's no progress yet.

685
00:26:07,010 --> 00:26:08,270
I'll keep an eye on her.

686
00:26:10,970 --> 00:26:12,110
I thought
you wouldn't contact me proactively

687
00:26:12,110 --> 00:26:12,850
anymore.

688
00:26:13,580 --> 00:26:14,890
This is to thank you

689
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:16,920
for taking us inside to take photos.

690
00:26:18,540 --> 00:26:19,030
I don't like

691
00:26:19,030 --> 00:26:20,760
making friends with a purpose.

692
00:26:22,230 --> 00:26:23,560
But once we're friends,

693
00:26:24,030 --> 00:26:26,430
isn't it normal
to help each other out a bit?

694
00:26:28,570 --> 00:26:29,770
That day at the mine,

695
00:26:30,180 --> 00:26:30,670
I saw you

696
00:26:30,700 --> 00:26:32,160
speaking so confidently.

697
00:26:32,790 --> 00:26:33,500
I didn't expect you

698
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:34,230
to be a leader

699
00:26:34,250 --> 00:26:35,980
who really knows the business.

700
00:26:36,980 --> 00:26:37,750
If I didn't,

701
00:26:37,770 --> 00:26:38,840
how could I work at the mine?

702
00:26:38,840 --> 00:26:40,500
Would the workers respect me?

703
00:26:41,860 --> 00:26:43,860
My brother said something similar.

704
00:26:46,910 --> 00:26:47,370
Yeah.

705
00:26:48,020 --> 00:26:50,110
He went from the army to the saltworks,

706
00:26:50,110 --> 00:26:51,230
and then to the coal mine.

707
00:26:51,230 --> 00:26:52,490
He had more to adapt to.

708
00:26:54,230 --> 00:26:55,450
It was harder for him.

709
00:26:56,180 --> 00:26:58,180
At least you're a college graduate.

710
00:26:58,850 --> 00:27:00,850
You mean a sports academy graduate.

711
00:27:01,230 --> 00:27:01,680
I only got

712
00:27:01,680 --> 00:27:03,140
an empty diploma from there.

713
00:27:03,140 --> 00:27:04,380
I'm uncultured.

714
00:27:06,070 --> 00:27:07,610
Last time I saw you holding the camera,

715
00:27:07,610 --> 00:27:09,070
you held it very steadily.

716
00:27:09,070 --> 00:27:09,980
Were you

717
00:27:10,010 --> 00:27:11,670
a weightlifter before?

718
00:27:12,780 --> 00:27:14,750
With my build? Weightlifting?

719
00:27:16,900 --> 00:27:17,340
Back then,

720
00:27:17,340 --> 00:27:18,300
we didn't have

721
00:27:18,330 --> 00:27:19,480
a weightlifting major.

722
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:20,940
I don't know if they do now.

723
00:27:22,250 --> 00:27:23,660
I trained in air rifle.

724
00:27:23,770 --> 00:27:24,420
Shooting.

725
00:27:25,100 --> 00:27:26,960
But I haven't practiced in years.

726
00:27:26,980 --> 00:27:28,910
I can only hold a camera steady now.

727
00:27:30,310 --> 00:27:31,700
You're quite honest.

728
00:27:32,980 --> 00:27:34,380
There's nothing to hide.

729
00:27:34,850 --> 00:27:35,640
Besides,

730
00:27:35,840 --> 00:27:37,180
you're a police officer.

731
00:27:37,180 --> 00:27:38,510
I can't fool you anyway.

732
00:27:41,740 --> 00:27:43,070
After you graduated
from the sports academy,

733
00:27:43,070 --> 00:27:44,800
have you ever fired a gun again?

734
00:27:45,210 --> 00:27:46,040
Fired a gun?

735
00:27:46,070 --> 00:27:47,400
Where can I even get one?

736
00:27:49,030 --> 00:27:50,890
What about the Uninhabited Zone?

737
00:27:53,120 --> 00:27:54,380
Have you been in there?

738
00:27:57,940 --> 00:27:58,830
You finally asked me

739
00:27:58,830 --> 00:27:59,510
about this.

740
00:27:59,940 --> 00:28:00,780
I did

741
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:02,130
go into that place once.

742
00:28:03,030 --> 00:28:04,080
As a fossicker.

743
00:28:04,500 --> 00:28:06,820
It was the first time
I wanted to touch a gun again

744
00:28:06,820 --> 00:28:07,690
and the first time

745
00:28:07,690 --> 00:28:09,750
I wanted to use a gun to shoot someone.

746
00:28:10,640 --> 00:28:11,820
I wanted to kill

747
00:28:11,850 --> 00:28:12,900
all the ringleaders,

748
00:28:12,900 --> 00:28:13,890
then escape

749
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:15,320
with the brothers there.

750
00:28:16,350 --> 00:28:18,080
After all, in a place like that,

751
00:28:18,460 --> 00:28:20,160
you don't even need to bury the bodies.

752
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:21,160
No one would know.

753
00:28:21,810 --> 00:28:24,010
Only the vultures in the sky would know.

754
00:28:27,070 --> 00:28:29,400
It's not illegal to think about it, right?

755
00:28:32,750 --> 00:28:33,250
Why did you

756
00:28:33,250 --> 00:28:34,900
enter Bolamula back then?

757
00:28:35,770 --> 00:28:37,660
Going there to make money,

758
00:28:37,980 --> 00:28:39,270
you may die

759
00:28:39,380 --> 00:28:40,710
before you can spend it.

760
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,480
I was young.

761
00:28:42,590 --> 00:28:43,990
I just wanted fast money.

762
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:46,840
I didn't have a family
to tie me down anyway.

763
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:47,810
But after I went in,

764
00:28:47,810 --> 00:28:49,000
I got scared.

765
00:28:49,090 --> 00:28:50,350
So I never wanted

766
00:28:50,530 --> 00:28:51,510
to go back again.

767
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:54,680
After that, I went to Guangdong to work.

768
00:28:54,680 --> 00:28:56,110
In the 90s,

769
00:28:56,200 --> 00:28:58,220
I heard it was developing fast there.

770
00:28:58,220 --> 00:28:59,160
After I went there, I realized

771
00:28:59,160 --> 00:29:01,360
there were indeed many opportunities,

772
00:29:01,390 --> 00:29:02,920
but none of them were for me.

773
00:29:09,280 --> 00:29:09,790
Excuse me.

774
00:29:09,790 --> 00:29:10,850
I need to take this.

775
00:29:13,660 --> 00:29:14,160
Hello?

776
00:29:15,140 --> 00:29:16,540
When are you coming back?

777
00:29:18,380 --> 00:29:19,580
I'm working overtime right now.

778
00:29:19,580 --> 00:29:20,780
Mom, have some water.

779
00:29:21,840 --> 00:29:23,160
Shao is here.

780
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:26,460
I heard that.

781
00:29:26,900 --> 00:29:28,830
He even bought you a birthday cake.

782
00:29:31,090 --> 00:29:31,920
I'm...

783
00:29:31,940 --> 00:29:32,480
Mom,

784
00:29:32,830 --> 00:29:34,410
you should come back later.

785
00:29:34,770 --> 00:29:36,500
Or you'll fight with Dad again.

786
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:37,050
Shush.

787
00:29:37,050 --> 00:29:37,700
Don't eat too much cake.

788
00:29:37,700 --> 00:29:38,330
Be quiet.

789
00:29:38,500 --> 00:29:39,110
Mom,

790
00:29:39,180 --> 00:29:40,510
keep an eye on her for me.

791
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:41,790
I know.

792
00:29:42,160 --> 00:29:43,190
Come back soon.

793
00:29:45,700 --> 00:29:47,160
She'll be back. In a while.

794
00:29:47,500 --> 00:29:48,070
It's fine.

795
00:29:48,070 --> 00:29:49,020
No rush.

796
00:29:54,650 --> 00:29:56,810
Officer Bai, you're really dedicated.

797
00:29:56,810 --> 00:29:59,070
You're working overtime to question me.

798
00:29:59,270 --> 00:30:00,170
Then next time,

799
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:02,140
should I just invite you to my office?

800
00:30:02,140 --> 00:30:03,470
Well...

801
00:30:04,320 --> 00:30:05,340
then you'll need...

802
00:30:05,340 --> 00:30:06,400
an arrest warrant.

803
00:30:08,330 --> 00:30:09,030
Alright.

804
00:30:09,070 --> 00:30:10,930
I'll treat you to a meal sometime.

805
00:30:12,070 --> 00:30:13,130
I'll send you home.

806
00:30:14,510 --> 00:30:14,940
Okay.

807
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:35,770
Where are you going?

808
00:30:37,640 --> 00:30:39,220
Women are not easy to fool.

809
00:30:39,880 --> 00:30:42,740
Female police officers
are more difficult to fool.

810
00:30:44,460 --> 00:30:45,270
Meng Yaohui.

811
00:30:46,160 --> 00:30:47,220
What are you doing?

812
00:30:48,070 --> 00:30:49,470
I'm taking you to a place.

813
00:30:50,130 --> 00:30:51,990
Work overtime a bit longer, okay?

814
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:11,110
Sometimes when work gets annoying,

815
00:31:11,110 --> 00:31:12,060
I come here alone

816
00:31:12,090 --> 00:31:13,020
to clear my head.

817
00:31:14,380 --> 00:31:15,580
It's sort of an oasis.

818
00:31:17,320 --> 00:31:19,650
Why are you being so poetic
all of a sudden?

819
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:21,630
Don't tell people

820
00:31:21,660 --> 00:31:23,260
you're uncultured anymore.

821
00:31:23,790 --> 00:31:25,090
This is an oasis.

822
00:31:26,550 --> 00:31:27,050
Really.

823
00:31:28,700 --> 00:31:29,680
What do you mean?

824
00:31:31,220 --> 00:31:32,110
This

825
00:31:32,310 --> 00:31:33,150
used to be

826
00:31:33,180 --> 00:31:34,510
a bare, barren hill.

827
00:31:35,420 --> 00:31:37,220
Our group handled the greening.

828
00:31:38,750 --> 00:31:39,500
That was the first project

829
00:31:39,500 --> 00:31:41,030
I was in charge of at Xinhai.

830
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:44,930
Profit is the only motivation.

831
00:31:45,010 --> 00:31:45,790
Don't tell me your boss

832
00:31:45,790 --> 00:31:46,850
your boss actually has

833
00:31:46,850 --> 00:31:48,250
environmental ideals.

834
00:31:48,830 --> 00:31:49,460
Well,

835
00:31:49,970 --> 00:31:50,950
he doesn't.

836
00:31:53,640 --> 00:31:54,680
The company originally wanted to build

837
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:55,940
a city park.

838
00:31:56,530 --> 00:31:58,590
The group wanted to develop tourism.

839
00:31:58,750 --> 00:31:59,550
But Tianduo

840
00:31:59,570 --> 00:32:00,340
really doesn't have much

841
00:32:00,340 --> 00:32:01,470
tourism potential,

842
00:32:01,490 --> 00:32:02,420
so we dropped it.

843
00:32:03,610 --> 00:32:04,250
True.

844
00:32:04,790 --> 00:32:05,990
Just dig more coal,

845
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:07,270
and the money for greening

846
00:32:07,270 --> 00:32:08,400
will be earned back.

847
00:32:13,840 --> 00:32:15,730
Judge by results, not intentions.

848
00:32:15,730 --> 00:32:17,390
No matter the starting point,

849
00:32:17,420 --> 00:32:19,120
this hill is green now.

850
00:32:20,740 --> 00:32:21,250
Isn't that

851
00:32:21,250 --> 00:32:22,350
a good thing?

852
00:32:23,900 --> 00:32:25,010
Just like

853
00:32:25,900 --> 00:32:26,740
when Duojie started

854
00:32:26,740 --> 00:32:27,770
the Mazhi Economic Development Company,

855
00:32:27,770 --> 00:32:28,490
it was not

856
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:29,980
for wildlife protection.

857
00:32:30,090 --> 00:32:30,920
But in the end,

858
00:32:30,940 --> 00:32:31,930
you really promoted

859
00:32:31,930 --> 00:32:33,860
the establishment of the reserve.

860
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:36,200
Sometimes

861
00:32:36,660 --> 00:32:37,600
the starting point and the process

862
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:38,490
may deviate,

863
00:32:39,370 --> 00:32:41,100
but the result is what matters,

864
00:32:41,210 --> 00:32:41,660
right?

865
00:32:59,070 --> 00:32:59,940
Work?

866
00:33:07,290 --> 00:33:09,220
You're actually hiding it from me.

867
00:33:13,340 --> 00:33:14,340
It's from a woman.

868
00:33:15,250 --> 00:33:15,910
Want to see?

869
00:33:16,370 --> 00:33:16,830
No need.

870
00:33:17,250 --> 00:33:18,230
I'm not interested

871
00:33:18,230 --> 00:33:19,490
in your romantic life.

872
00:33:19,840 --> 00:33:21,240
Unless it involves vice.

873
00:33:33,270 --> 00:33:34,200
Happy Birthday.

874
00:33:38,350 --> 00:33:38,980
Thanks.

875
00:33:50,270 --> 00:33:51,160
How is it going?

876
00:33:51,790 --> 00:33:53,380
Things are stable here for now.

877
00:33:53,380 --> 00:33:54,250
Work?

878
00:33:55,980 --> 00:33:56,980
It's from a woman.

879
00:33:57,270 --> 00:33:57,930
Want to see?

880
00:34:06,790 --> 00:34:07,290
Mom.

881
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:11,070
Zhuling ate all the cake.

882
00:34:13,050 --> 00:34:13,650
Yes.

883
00:34:14,440 --> 00:34:15,199
Fine.

884
00:34:16,500 --> 00:34:17,610
When Bai Ju comes back

885
00:34:17,610 --> 00:34:18,810
and demands answers,

886
00:34:19,110 --> 00:34:20,310
I'll let her find you.

887
00:34:21,920 --> 00:34:22,780
It was my fault.

888
00:34:24,010 --> 00:34:25,070
I'm soft-hearted.

889
00:34:28,120 --> 00:34:29,070
Do you plan to just

890
00:34:29,070 --> 00:34:30,469
keep visiting like this?

891
00:34:34,300 --> 00:34:35,280
Well,

892
00:34:36,929 --> 00:34:38,360
it's not up to me.

893
00:34:38,510 --> 00:34:39,460
It's up to Bai Ju.

894
00:34:39,980 --> 00:34:41,580
I rented the place for a year.

895
00:34:41,590 --> 00:34:43,010
Visiting for a year is fine,

896
00:34:43,010 --> 00:34:44,870
but I can't keep visting forever.

897
00:34:47,090 --> 00:34:48,320
All these years,

898
00:34:48,880 --> 00:34:50,340
I've never said anything,

899
00:34:51,570 --> 00:34:53,150
mostly because there hasn't been

900
00:34:53,150 --> 00:34:54,380
a right time.

901
00:34:55,510 --> 00:34:57,240
You said things between us didn't change,

902
00:34:57,240 --> 00:34:59,240
and that you would still call me Mom.

903
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:00,840
No matter what you think,

904
00:35:01,730 --> 00:35:02,820
in my heart—

905
00:35:04,150 --> 00:35:05,350
let me put it this way—

906
00:35:05,940 --> 00:35:07,460
even if you two

907
00:35:07,510 --> 00:35:09,640
start your own families in the future,

908
00:35:09,990 --> 00:35:10,770
I still consider you

909
00:35:10,770 --> 00:35:11,910
my own child.

910
00:35:17,070 --> 00:35:17,570
Mom.

911
00:35:21,480 --> 00:35:21,820
The separation

912
00:35:21,820 --> 00:35:23,700
wasn't either of your fault.

913
00:35:25,690 --> 00:35:26,690
Before,

914
00:35:27,820 --> 00:35:30,280
you took
a three-year assignment for Bai Ju.

915
00:35:31,070 --> 00:35:32,380
After you went back,

916
00:35:32,420 --> 00:35:34,290
you waited years for her.

917
00:35:34,620 --> 00:35:36,440
You've been very patient.

918
00:35:38,130 --> 00:35:39,210
But some things

919
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,130
depend on fate.

920
00:35:42,780 --> 00:35:44,050
You can't force them.

921
00:35:47,710 --> 00:35:48,150
I wasn't

922
00:35:48,150 --> 00:35:49,700
always mature either.

923
00:35:52,570 --> 00:35:53,860
I knew Bai Ju

924
00:35:54,780 --> 00:35:56,110
wanted to stay in Mazhi,

925
00:35:58,510 --> 00:35:59,610
but I kept urging her

926
00:35:59,610 --> 00:36:01,410
to go to the provincial capital.

927
00:36:01,680 --> 00:36:02,930
It made us

928
00:36:03,050 --> 00:36:04,450
unhappy whenever we met.

929
00:36:05,530 --> 00:36:06,880
So I came back this time

930
00:36:07,570 --> 00:36:09,130
to help her find the truth,

931
00:36:10,420 --> 00:36:12,550
and then we can move forward together.

932
00:36:14,390 --> 00:36:15,270
So I...

933
00:36:17,720 --> 00:36:18,660
Look at her.

934
00:36:18,700 --> 00:36:19,790
She's a mother now,

935
00:36:19,860 --> 00:36:21,190
but still so forgetful.

936
00:36:21,710 --> 00:36:22,160
Yes.

937
00:36:26,970 --> 00:36:28,510
It's late. I should go.

938
00:36:29,670 --> 00:36:31,400
You left your key at the office?

939
00:36:34,550 --> 00:36:35,300
Mom.

940
00:36:35,550 --> 00:36:36,590
Why are you back?

941
00:36:36,650 --> 00:36:37,820
You're still awake?

942
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:42,020
Shao, you're here too?

943
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:43,340
Shao.

944
00:36:44,460 --> 00:36:45,360
What are you waiting for?

945
00:36:45,360 --> 00:36:47,090
Come help me with these things.

946
00:36:48,230 --> 00:36:49,690
What are you doing?

947
00:36:50,210 --> 00:36:51,320
It's fine that you didn't tell us

948
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:52,110
the small things,

949
00:36:52,110 --> 00:36:52,830
but something this big—

950
00:36:52,830 --> 00:36:54,300
you didn't tell the family either?

951
00:36:54,300 --> 00:36:55,030
Exactly.

952
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:57,170
Have you thought this through?

953
00:36:57,380 --> 00:36:58,360
Let me tell you,

954
00:36:58,580 --> 00:36:59,580
I don't agree!

955
00:36:59,980 --> 00:37:02,960
There's nothing you can do.

956
00:37:02,980 --> 00:37:04,870
We're already divorced.

957
00:37:06,010 --> 00:37:06,400
Mom,

958
00:37:06,450 --> 00:37:07,710
which room am I staying in?

959
00:37:07,710 --> 00:37:08,910
There's no room for you here.

960
00:37:08,910 --> 00:37:10,040
Don't try to fool me.

961
00:37:10,440 --> 00:37:12,110
Your new house has 3 bedrooms.

962
00:37:12,440 --> 00:37:13,110
One for you,

963
00:37:13,210 --> 00:37:14,010
one for Bai Ju.

964
00:37:14,090 --> 00:37:14,500
Isn't

965
00:37:14,530 --> 00:37:15,510
the remaining one mine?

966
00:37:15,510 --> 00:37:16,400
I know it.

967
00:37:17,960 --> 00:37:18,550
Why aren't you using

968
00:37:18,550 --> 00:37:19,210
this air purifier

969
00:37:19,210 --> 00:37:20,170
I bought for you?

970
00:37:20,260 --> 00:37:21,290
It can run all day

971
00:37:21,320 --> 00:37:22,340
automatically.

972
00:37:24,210 --> 00:37:25,740
It's none of your business.

973
00:37:25,990 --> 00:37:26,300
You...

974
00:37:26,300 --> 00:37:27,360
Alright, alright.

975
00:37:27,670 --> 00:37:28,530
Sit down first.

976
00:37:28,770 --> 00:37:30,100
Sit down and let's talk.

977
00:37:30,800 --> 00:37:31,600
One's single,

978
00:37:31,950 --> 00:37:32,880
one's divorced.

979
00:37:33,290 --> 00:37:34,950
Now another one got divorced.

980
00:37:36,990 --> 00:37:38,840
The one I worried about the most—

981
00:37:39,530 --> 00:37:40,280
Bai Ji—

982
00:37:40,860 --> 00:37:42,610
looks the most stable now.

983
00:37:43,630 --> 00:37:45,030
Can't you learn from him?

984
00:37:45,110 --> 00:37:46,400
Aren't you single too?

985
00:37:46,680 --> 00:37:47,790
I'm a widow!

986
00:37:47,940 --> 00:37:48,940
Is that the same?

987
00:37:49,440 --> 00:37:50,040
Come on...

988
00:37:50,810 --> 00:37:51,750
Be nice.

989
00:37:58,550 --> 00:37:59,150
Mom,

990
00:38:00,830 --> 00:38:02,790
getting a divorce is my choice.

991
00:38:03,320 --> 00:38:03,940
I didn't need

992
00:38:03,940 --> 00:38:05,730
to ask for anyone's permission.

993
00:38:05,730 --> 00:38:07,830
Even if Ding Zhuoxi hadn't agreed,

994
00:38:07,940 --> 00:38:09,150
I would still have divorced him.

995
00:38:09,150 --> 00:38:10,590
You were the one who insisted

996
00:38:10,590 --> 00:38:11,520
on marrying him.

997
00:38:11,690 --> 00:38:12,880
And now you're the one

998
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:13,920
who had to get divorced.

999
00:38:13,920 --> 00:38:15,180
That was the old me.

1000
00:38:15,210 --> 00:38:16,920
The current me is the current me.

1001
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:17,580
And tell me,

1002
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:19,120
what kind of relationship

1003
00:38:19,120 --> 00:38:20,310
lasts forever?

1004
00:38:24,420 --> 00:38:25,130
Of course,

1005
00:38:25,740 --> 00:38:27,340
family love is an exception.

1006
00:38:28,120 --> 00:38:29,500
I've always loved you.

1007
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:31,470
The bond of blood is eternal,

1008
00:38:31,470 --> 00:38:32,130
right?

1009
00:38:32,860 --> 00:38:33,380
Shao,

1010
00:38:35,090 --> 00:38:35,880
Did Xi

1011
00:38:35,900 --> 00:38:36,800
cheat on you?

1012
00:38:40,340 --> 00:38:41,160
No.

1013
00:38:41,190 --> 00:38:41,860
Really?

1014
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:46,570
Really, no.

1015
00:38:49,170 --> 00:38:50,550
These past few years,

1016
00:38:50,880 --> 00:38:51,920
we've just been

1017
00:38:51,960 --> 00:38:53,340
busy with our own things.

1018
00:38:53,340 --> 00:38:55,740
He's been running between here and abroad,

1019
00:38:56,020 --> 00:38:58,210
and I've been busy with my clothing brand.

1020
00:38:58,210 --> 00:38:59,360
Now that Dan

1021
00:38:59,390 --> 00:39:00,660
is studying abroad,

1022
00:39:01,290 --> 00:39:02,640
Ding wants to emigrate.

1023
00:39:03,770 --> 00:39:04,950
I don't want to go.

1024
00:39:06,570 --> 00:39:07,770
For things like this,

1025
00:39:07,880 --> 00:39:09,670
no one should compromise.

1026
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:12,570
So we just separated.

1027
00:39:22,650 --> 00:39:24,510
Wasn't that what you thought too?

1028
00:39:24,710 --> 00:39:26,510
Don't drag your sister into this.

1029
00:39:26,510 --> 00:39:28,170
Your situation is different.

1030
00:39:31,340 --> 00:39:32,650
When two people are together,

1031
00:39:32,650 --> 00:39:34,510
you have to learn to give a little.

1032
00:39:34,780 --> 00:39:37,030
You need to compromise
when problems arise.

1033
00:39:37,030 --> 00:39:38,360
Mom.

1034
00:39:38,650 --> 00:39:40,420
Times have changed.

1035
00:39:40,510 --> 00:39:41,610
Now it's about

1036
00:39:41,710 --> 00:39:43,780
realizing personal value.

1037
00:39:44,360 --> 00:39:45,190
And in which area

1038
00:39:45,190 --> 00:39:46,850
have you realized your value?

1039
00:39:47,400 --> 00:39:47,860
My daughter

1040
00:39:47,860 --> 00:39:49,200
has grown up.

1041
00:39:49,380 --> 00:39:50,860
And I have a successful career.

1042
00:39:50,860 --> 00:39:52,860
Doesn't that count as having value?

1043
00:39:52,860 --> 00:39:53,280
Fine, fine.

1044
00:39:53,280 --> 00:39:53,960
You have value.

1045
00:39:53,960 --> 00:39:55,290
You have the most value.

1046
00:39:58,380 --> 00:39:59,820
I'm doing pretty good.

1047
00:40:00,340 --> 00:40:01,940
Why is she angry?

1048
00:40:04,050 --> 00:40:05,710
Wait, Mom. What are you doing?

1049
00:40:07,500 --> 00:40:08,440
Mom.

1050
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:10,000
If someone has to stay in a hotel,

1051
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:11,330
let me go, okay?

1052
00:40:13,800 --> 00:40:15,150
What is this?

1053
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:18,520
Are you planning to live under a bridge?

1054
00:40:18,590 --> 00:40:20,120
Don't cause trouble for me.

1055
00:40:20,700 --> 00:40:21,240
Don't make yourself

1056
00:40:21,240 --> 00:40:22,410
look so miserable.

1057
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:23,610
Okay?

1058
00:40:24,570 --> 00:40:25,340
Mom. Mom.

1059
00:40:25,620 --> 00:40:27,020
Aren't you going to help?

1060
00:40:28,440 --> 00:40:30,480
A scientific expedition team
is coming from Beijing.

1061
00:40:30,480 --> 00:40:31,300
Mrs. Zhang is joining the team

1062
00:40:31,300 --> 00:40:32,900
to provide medical support.

1063
00:40:33,210 --> 00:40:33,900
Hurry up and help

1064
00:40:33,900 --> 00:40:34,950
pack the suitcase.

1065
00:40:34,950 --> 00:40:35,950
Again?

1066
00:40:37,670 --> 00:40:38,240
Are you the only one allowed

1067
00:40:38,240 --> 00:40:40,040
to realize your personal value?

1068
00:40:45,180 --> 00:40:46,140
Sister Bai Shao.

1069
00:40:47,300 --> 00:40:48,830
It's good that you're back.

1070
00:40:49,730 --> 00:40:50,480
No matter how good it is outside,

1071
00:40:50,480 --> 00:40:51,800
it's not as good as home.

1072
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:52,300
Yes.

1073
00:40:58,280 --> 00:40:59,210
Sister Bai Shao.

1074
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:00,960
Have some butter tea.

1075
00:41:01,060 --> 00:41:02,450
You also call me Sister?

1076
00:41:03,670 --> 00:41:04,330
Do I look

1077
00:41:04,360 --> 00:41:05,090
very old now?

1078
00:41:05,440 --> 00:41:06,640
No, no. It's not that.

1079
00:41:08,150 --> 00:41:09,740
It just slipped out.

1080
00:41:11,670 --> 00:41:12,270
Thank you.

1081
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:18,740
Where did you buy this?

1082
00:41:19,550 --> 00:41:20,440
I brought this back

1083
00:41:20,440 --> 00:41:22,360
from my self-driving tour in South Asia.

1084
00:41:22,360 --> 00:41:23,200
If you like it,

1085
00:41:23,220 --> 00:41:23,880
it's yours.

1086
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:26,010
Look.

1087
00:41:26,610 --> 00:41:28,010
It looks so much like you.

1088
00:41:30,530 --> 00:41:31,420
How?

1089
00:41:32,780 --> 00:41:33,760
The eyes.

1090
00:41:34,160 --> 00:41:35,290
They're twinkling.

1091
00:41:35,360 --> 00:41:35,990
Yes, yes.

1092
00:41:36,530 --> 00:41:37,320
Twinkling.

1093
00:41:39,010 --> 00:41:39,570
Shao,

1094
00:41:40,150 --> 00:41:41,380
go out and feed the horse, will you?

1095
00:41:41,380 --> 00:41:42,650
Go for a ride later.

1096
00:41:42,770 --> 00:41:43,410
Okay.

1097
00:41:45,670 --> 00:41:46,800
Does it look like me?

1098
00:41:47,590 --> 00:41:48,440
Yes.

1099
00:41:48,480 --> 00:41:50,150
Especially the nose.

1100
00:41:51,190 --> 00:41:52,800
You're asking for a beating.

1101
00:41:53,430 --> 00:41:54,240
You guys talk.

1102
00:42:18,860 --> 00:42:20,320
I talked myself raw.

1103
00:42:20,880 --> 00:42:21,990
I tried to get close to them

1104
00:42:21,990 --> 00:42:23,120
and gave them gifts.

1105
00:42:23,710 --> 00:42:24,760
I almost emptied

1106
00:42:24,780 --> 00:42:25,760
Sangba's

1107
00:42:25,910 --> 00:42:26,680
brother-in-law's

1108
00:42:26,680 --> 00:42:27,340
warehouse.

1109
00:42:27,800 --> 00:42:29,210
I found out about 5 of them.

1110
00:42:29,210 --> 00:42:30,390
3 have moved

1111
00:42:30,530 --> 00:42:31,660
to other provinces.

1112
00:42:32,320 --> 00:42:33,520
I've listed them all.

1113
00:42:34,780 --> 00:42:36,190
One's in Mazhi

1114
00:42:36,300 --> 00:42:38,150
doing odd jobs. He does everything—

1115
00:42:38,150 --> 00:42:39,600
plastering, puttying,

1116
00:42:40,050 --> 00:42:41,250
even forging stamps.

1117
00:42:41,320 --> 00:42:42,310
When I found him,

1118
00:42:42,340 --> 00:42:44,000
he was cooking in the kitchen.

1119
00:42:44,470 --> 00:42:45,450
The one

1120
00:42:45,690 --> 00:42:47,460
with a box drawn around the name

1121
00:42:47,550 --> 00:42:49,010
passed away two years ago.

1122
00:42:49,530 --> 00:42:50,710
What about the 6th one?

1123
00:42:50,710 --> 00:42:51,510
He's missing.

1124
00:42:51,880 --> 00:42:53,110
He's nowhere to be found.

1125
00:42:53,110 --> 00:42:54,280
I asked a few people.

1126
00:42:53,850 --> 00:42:55,670
[Disappeared? Wang Fumin]
[No news after 1998]

1127
00:42:54,310 --> 00:42:55,360
They said

1128
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:58,530
there's been no news of him

1129
00:42:58,860 --> 00:42:59,850
since 1998.

1130
00:43:01,420 --> 00:43:01,830
Then

1131
00:43:01,860 --> 00:43:03,390
pay special attention to this person.

1132
00:43:03,390 --> 00:43:04,140
Okay.
